body:
Huge thanks to zicuri for making his post about the idea of his, link to discussion-->https://avicus.net/forums/discussions/79c097ac7

Anyways, I completely agree with zicuri as his idea could be revolutionary if he can put it in to place! So....What did zicuri say that made me and other players hyped? He says about how there should be a tournament, but not with just a single server, multiple! Like teams from Badlion and Avicus could brawl it out in some gamemode they have in common. Put it this way, Hershy and Nestle battle because both products use cocoa powder, or in PVP terms, MineHQ vs PvpLounge because they both are large potpvp networks.


Preeeety excited eh? Well, how are we going to choose player(s) for the showdown? This is where my idea might come into place!


For an example, I'm going to do Avicus vs Stratus
Also, for starters, each server must have a common gamemode :D

Also we could include money into this :D Ok, We all know that some servers don't have enough money and need a lending hand, so we should start off with small prize pool, but it has to benefit the server and tourney winners, like if tourney winners get $10 and the server gets the rest, That wouldn't be fair would it? Maybe the prize pool can be $200,  Avicus pay $100 and Stratus does the same,

Then each server holds a tournament, the team that wins Avicus's tournament will go against the winners of Status's tournament, pretty much Team Bagelz ( avicus ) vs Team Donutz ( Stratus ).

Then the winner takes the $200

Maybe the winners can take $100 and the server takes$100, its a win win for everyone! Also it is a easy buck for servers that need a lending hand! I know there is many flaws and holes, but maybe the staff can figure it out,
anyways

~Clickn out                          BTW Idk about team sizes, maybe 4 or 2 is ok :D

But hey, keep making good ideas maybe something from you can work out :)
